Add public-ish SDL_DOSVesaDirect* functions in
include/SDL3/SDL_dosvesa_directaccess.h that let DOS callers (e.g.
NXEngine-evo's Renderer::flip()) bypass SDL_RenderPresent and
SDL_UpdateWindowSurface, calling the SDL3-DOS framebuffer flush
primitives directly while preserving SDL3's mode management, DPMI
mapping, palette sync, and Cirrus auto-disable heuristics.

Background — wave 18's measured lever:

Real-HW measurements (PODP83 + Cirrus + UNIVBE 6.7) show that on top
of the actual VRAM write, SDL_RenderPresent + SDL_UpdateWindowSurface
add ~5 ms / flip — ~13 % of the 38.7 ms / flip budget at 25.9 fps
title. The cost lives upstream of DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer (in
SDL_RenderPresent's SW-renderer queue flush + the
SDL_UpdateWindowSurface state machine), so optimizing the existing
fast path inside DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer can't reclaim it.
The wave-18 lever is to bypass these layers entirely from engine
code and call the same dosmemput / banked-flush primitives that
DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer would have called.

API surface (workspace-local; never upstreamed per
sdl_ai_policy memory):

- SDL_DOSVesaDirectState          — POD snapshot of fb_state
                                    (LFB ptr, banked window metadata,
                                    fb_size, page_offset forward-compat)
- SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetState       — populate snapshot from fb_state
- SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetGeneration  — Uint32 mode-change counter; bumps
                                    on invalidate / populate-success /
                                    DestroyWindowFramebuffer; signals
                                    both fb_state-changed AND
                                    window->surface-may-have-changed
- SDL_DOSVesaDirectSwitchBank     — wrap SwitchBank() (existing inline)
- SDL_DOSVesaDirectBankedFlush    — wrap BankedDosmemput() (existing inline)
- SDL_DOSVesaDirectProgramPalette — wrap ProgramVGADAC() for INDEX8 DAC sync
- SDL_DOSVesaDirectPresentFull    — convenience: cheapest full-screen present
- SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_DIRECT_VESA   — hint name; engine-side gating only
                                    (SDL itself does not consume it)

Engine integration FAQ baked into header doc-comments:

- "SDL_FlushRenderer vs SDL_RenderPresent": engines using a SW
  renderer should call SDL_FlushRenderer() before invoking the
  direct-VESA path. FlushRenderer = FlushRenderCommands +
  InvalidateCachedState; that drains the queue into
  window->surface->pixels and is in fact slightly more thorough on
  the renderer side than SDL_RenderPresent (which skips
  InvalidateCachedState). The piece RenderPresent does that
  FlushRenderer doesn't is renderer->RenderPresent → SW_RenderPresent
  → SDL_UpdateWindowSurface → DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer —
  exactly the chain we want to bypass. Engines hand-rolling all
  drawcalls directly into window->surface->pixels (Lever B) can skip
  FlushRenderer entirely.
- "window->surface re-allocation timing": every code path that
  destroys + recreates window->surface ALSO re-runs
  CreateWindowFramebuffer → populate_fb_state_for_direct_fb, which
  bumps the generation counter here. So generation bump signals BOTH
  fb_state changed AND window->surface->pixels may have moved. No
  separate heartbeat SDL_RenderPresent is needed for correctness.
- "Per-flip housekeeping": current_bank in
  DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer is a function-local automatic, NOT
  a static. Engine direct path's per-call current_bank=-1 init is
  correct: chip-side bank state at flush start is irrelevant
  because the first SwitchBank always hits the bank!=*current_bank
  branch. WaitForVBlank / cursor logic / page-flip BIOS call only
  fire on the normal path; fast path (and engine direct path) skip
  them by design. Palette DAC sync is replicated via
  SDL_DOSVesaDirectProgramPalette.

Implementation notes:

- The bank-switch + dosmemput primitives stay SDL_FORCE_INLINE static;
  the public functions are thin same-TU wrappers so both paths
  benefit from the same wave-14-thru-33 debugging (display-start
  query, bank-1 offset fix, LFB sentinel, etc).

- Generation counter is a static Uint32 in SDL_dosframebuffer.c,
  bumped in DOSVESA_InvalidateCachedFramebuffer (mode change),
  populate_fb_state_for_direct_fb (success path, including lazy-
  reinit and CreateWindowFramebuffer's fast-path branch), and
  DOSVESA_DestroyWindowFramebuffer (window destruction). Single-
  threaded backend — no atomics needed.

- Forward-compat: page_offset field always 0 in the current single-
  buffered build (post-patch 0014); engine adds it to its
  dst_offset / vram_ptr arithmetic so a future page-flip revival
  needs no engine-side change.

- Hint changes (PREFER_LFB / DISABLE_LFB / FORCE_LFB) do NOT bump
  the generation counter — those are read at mode-set / lazy-reinit
  time and require a restart. Documented in the header.

- Cursor compositing intentionally NOT exposed — Cave Story doesn't
  use the system mouse cursor in gameplay, and the cursor logic is
  the bulk of the SDL3-DOS normal path (which we're bypassing).

The header drops into include/SDL3/ and is automatically picked up
by CMake's existing file(GLOB SDL3_INCLUDE_FILES …/include/SDL3/*.h)
at vendor/SDL/CMakeLists.txt:3769 — no CMakeLists.txt edit needed.

The companion engine-side patch (nxengine/0086) consumes this API to
implement Renderer::_direct_vesa_present() + flip() integration; see
docs/PHASE9-WAVE-17-18-PLAN.md § 4 for the wave-18 plan.

DOSKUTSU local patch (workspace-local; never upstreamed).
