+/**
+ * # CategoryDOSVesaDirectAccess
+ *
+ * **DOSKUTSU local addition (patches/SDL/0034, never upstreamed).** This
+ * header is part of the SDL3-DOS backend's "direct-VESA" escape hatch — an
+ * API for DOS callers (engines, demos) that want to skip the
+ * SDL_RenderPresent → SDL_UpdateWindowSurface → DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer
+ * dance and write pixels directly into the VESA framebuffer.
+ *
+ * On the doskutsu Cave Story port, real-HW measurements at title-screen
+ * steady state on a Pentium OverDrive 83 MHz + Cirrus + UNIVBE 6.7 show the
+ * SDL_RenderPresent path costs ~5 ms / flip beyond the actual VRAM write.
+ * That's ~13 % of the 38.7 ms / flip budget at 25.9 fps. The wave-18 lever
+ * exposes the existing SDL3-DOS flush primitives (SwitchBank,
+ * BankedDosmemput, ProgramVGADAC) so the engine can call them directly,
+ * preserving SDL3's mode management + DPMI mapping + Cirrus auto-disable
+ * heuristics while bypassing the SDL_RenderPresent state-machine cost.
+ *
+ * ## When to use this
+ *
+ * **Only on DOS, only when you've already tuned the SDL_RenderPresent path
+ * and need the last few percent.** A normal SDL3 app calling
+ * `SDL_UpdateWindowSurface` already lands in the same VRAM-write code under
+ * the hood (via DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer's fast path when
+ * `SDL_HINT_DOS_ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER=1`). This API is the further step
+ * — bypassing the SDL renderer/window machinery entirely.
+ *
+ * ## Lifecycle
+ *
+ * 1. Set `SDL_HINT_DOS_ALLOW_DIRECT_FRAMEBUFFER=1` before window creation.
+ * 2. Create your SDL_Window + SDL_Surface as usual. SDL3-DOS populates its
+ *    fast-path cache at `SDL_GetWindowSurface()` (or first
+ *    `SDL_UpdateWindowSurface()` via lazy-reinit, see patch 0011).
+ * 3. Call SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetState() to snapshot the cache. If it returns
+ *    false, fall back to SDL_UpdateWindowSurface — the fast path isn't
+ *    engaged (no usable VBE access path, hint not set, etc).
+ * 4. **Resolve renderer queue into the window surface FIRST.** If you've
+ *    been issuing SDL_Render* drawcalls into a renderer whose target is
+ *    the window's surface (typical SW renderer setup), call
+ *    SDL_FlushRenderer() to drain the command queue into
+ *    `window->surface->pixels` before reading those pixels here. This
+ *    is the equivalent of SDL_RenderPresent's first phase
+ *    (FlushRenderCommands) without its second phase (the SW renderer's
+ *    SW_RenderPresent → SDL_UpdateWindowSurface → DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer
+ *    chain that we are deliberately bypassing). SDL_FlushRenderer also
+ *    calls renderer->InvalidateCachedState which is the only renderer-side
+ *    cleanup SDL_RenderPresent does NOT do — so SDL_FlushRenderer is in
+ *    fact slightly more thorough on the renderer side. Engines that hand-
+ *    roll all their drawcalls directly into `window->surface->pixels`
+ *    (e.g. NXEngine-evo's Lever B primitives) can skip this step
+ *    entirely; the surface pixels are already authoritative.
+ * 5. On each flip:
+ *    - Compare SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetGeneration() against your cached
+ *      generation; re-snapshot if it bumped (mode change, lazy-reinit,
+ *      or window-surface destroy/recreate — see "Mode-change semantics"
+ *      below for the full list of triggers).
+ *    - For LFB path (use_dosmemput=false): `SDL_memcpy(vram_ptr +
+ *      page_offset, pixels, fb_size)`.
+ *    - For banked single-bank: `dosmemput(pixels, fb_size, vram_phys +
+ *      page_offset)`.
+ *    - For banked multi-bank: SDL_DOSVesaDirectBankedFlush().
+ *    - If your INDEX8 palette changed: SDL_DOSVesaDirectProgramPalette().
+ * 6. Do NOT call SDL_RenderPresent or SDL_UpdateWindowSurface in the same
+ *    flip. They'd re-flush the (now-stale) window surface to VRAM,
+ *    overwriting your direct write.
+ *
+ * The helpers (SDL_DOSVesaDirectSwitchBank, SDL_DOSVesaDirectBankedFlush)
+ * are thin wrappers around the existing internal SwitchBank() and
+ * BankedDosmemput() primitives in SDL_dosframebuffer.c. Reusing them means
+ * direct-VESA callers benefit from the same bank-switch debugging
+ * (patches 0014/0018/0019/0029) without reimplementing the math.
+ *
+ * ## Caller-owned perf instrumentation
+ *
+ * The "fastpath-timing block" emitted by DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer
+ * (patch 0015) does NOT fire on the direct path — DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer
+ * is bypassed entirely. Callers that want per-flip ms timing must instrument
+ * their own present routine (e.g. SDL_GetPerformanceCounter brackets around
+ * the dosmemput / memcpy, summary lines every N flips). See
+ * docs/PHASE9-WAVE-17-18-PLAN.md § 4.
+ *
+ * ## Mode-change semantics
+ *
+ * SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetGeneration() is a monotonically-increasing counter
+ * bumped whenever the cached fb_state changes underneath callers.
+ * Specifically the counter is bumped on:
+ *
+ *   - DOSVESA_InvalidateCachedFramebuffer (called from SetDisplayMode
+ *     before freeing the DPMI mapping; mode change is the prototype
+ *     trigger).
+ *   - populate_fb_state_for_direct_fb success path (called from both
+ *     CreateWindowFramebuffer at window creation AND from
+ *     UpdateWindowFramebuffer's lazy-reinit when fb_state was previously
+ *     invalidated — see patch 0011).
+ *   - DOSVESA_DestroyWindowFramebuffer (window destruction).
+ *
+ * Compare against your cached value each flip; on mismatch, re-snapshot.
+ * The counter is `Uint32` — wrapping is theoretically possible but a
+ * 32-bit counter at one bump per mode-change is good for billions of
+ * mode-changes; in practice we mode-change once at startup and once on
+ * quit.
+ *
+ * **Important: window->surface re-allocation.** SDL3 may destroy and
+ * recreate `window->surface` (the system-RAM source surface the engine
+ * has been blitting into) when `window->surface_valid` clears.
+ * Triggers include `SDL_OnWindowPixelSizeChanged`, explicit
+ * `SDL_DestroyWindowSurface`, and the SDL_GetWindowSurface() recreate
+ * branch. Critically: **every path that re-allocates `window->surface`
+ * also re-runs DOSVESA_CreateWindowFramebuffer →
+ * populate_fb_state_for_direct_fb, which bumps the generation here.**
+ * So a generation bump signals BOTH "fb_state changed" AND
+ * "window->surface->pixels pointer may have changed" simultaneously,
+ * and engine code that re-snapshots state on generation change ALSO
+ * needs to re-fetch its `window->surface` pointer in the same step.
+ * No separate heartbeat call (e.g. periodic SDL_RenderPresent) is
+ * needed for correctness — the generation counter alone is sufficient.
+ * (A periodic heartbeat is still useful for diagnostic visibility, but
+ * not for synchronization.)
+ *
+ * The hint-driven path-selection (SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB,
+ * SDL_HINT_DOS_DISABLE_LFB, SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_LFB) is read at
+ * mode-set / lazy-reinit time and DOES NOT bump the generation counter.
+ * Restart the app to apply hint changes.
+ *
+ * ## Per-flip coordination — no SDL-side housekeeping needed
+ *
+ * The `current_bank` memoization variable in DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer
+ * is a function-local automatic, NOT a static. Each call initializes it
+ * fresh to -1 before the banked-write loop and discards it on return.
+ * Engine direct-VESA callers do the same (init to -1 once per flip,
+ * pass through to SwitchBank / BankedFlush). The chip's physical bank
+ * state at flush start is irrelevant: the first SwitchBank call always
+ * compares `bank != *current_bank` (`bank=0, *current_bank=-1`) and
+ * issues the BIOS switch unconditionally. So the engine cannot
+ * "miss" a per-flip bank-reset that SDL would have done — there is
+ * no such reset to miss.
+ *
+ * Other per-flip work inside DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer:
+ *
+ *   - **WaitForVBlank** — only on the normal (non-fast) path. The
+ *     fast path skips it; engine direct path skips it the same way.
+ *   - **Cursor compositing** — only on the normal path. Skipped here
+ *     by design (Cave Story / NXEngine-evo doesn't use the system
+ *     cursor on DOS).
+ *   - **Palette DAC sync** — fast path checks
+ *     `palette->version != vdata->palette_version` and calls
+ *     ProgramVGADAC. Engine direct path replicates this via its own
+ *     remembered version + SDL_DOSVesaDirectProgramPalette().
+ *   - **Sentinel / audit diagnostic logs** — env-gated, periodic
+ *     (every 100 flushes), have no effect on chip state. Engine
+ *     direct path skips them; no functional miss.
+ *   - **Page-flip BIOS call (VBE 0x4F07)** — only on the LFB nearptr
+ *     path AND when `page_flip_available=true`. Patch 0014 force-
+ *     disabled `page_flip_available` so this is currently a no-op
+ *     branch. Engine skips with no behavioral change. The
+ *     `page_offset` snapshot field is the forward-compat hook for
+ *     when page-flip is re-enabled.
+ *   - **Timing brackets / counters** — diagnostic; engine should
+ *     instrument its own present routine independently (see
+ *     "Caller-owned perf instrumentation" below).
+ *
+ * In summary: an engine that owns palette sync (via
+ * SDL_DOSVesaDirectProgramPalette) and initializes `current_bank=-1`
+ * per flip already covers everything DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer's
+ * fast path does. Nothing further from the SDL side is required.
+ *
+ * ## Cursor compositing
+ *
+ * The direct-VESA path bypasses the cursor-compositing logic in the
+ * SDL3-DOS normal path entirely. Apps using the system mouse cursor on
+ * the DOS backend should NOT use this API. Cave Story / NXEngine-evo
+ * doesn't use the system cursor in gameplay, so this is fine for
+ * doskutsu's purposes.
+ *
+ * ## Threading
+ *
+ * The SDL3-DOS backend is single-threaded by design (cooperative DPMI
+ * scheduler; `std::thread` and `SDL_CreateThread` are forbidden in port
+ * glue). The direct-VESA snapshot is therefore not protected by any
+ * locks. Call SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetState() from the same thread that does
+ * the present writes.
+ *
+ * ## License + attribution
+ *
+ * This header is added by patches/SDL/0034 (DOSKUTSU local patch, never
+ * upstreamed). The bank-switch + dosmemput primitives it exposes are
+ * SDL3-DOS code; this header is a thin export layer. Patch policy is
+ * workspace-local per the project's sdl_ai_policy memory entry — these
+ * declarations are not contributed back to libsdl-org/SDL.
+ */
+
+#ifndef SDL_dosvesa_directaccess_h_
+#define SDL_dosvesa_directaccess_h_
+
+#include <SDL3/SDL_stdinc.h>
+#include <SDL3/SDL_pixels.h>
+
+#include <SDL3/SDL_begin_code.h>
+/* Set up for C function definitions, even when using C++ */
+#ifdef __cplusplus
+extern "C" {
+#endif
+
+/**
+ * Hint name registered for the SDL3-DOS direct-VESA fast path. SDL itself
+ * does not consume this hint — engine-side code reads it to gate whether
+ * the direct-VESA call sequence runs (vs falling back to
+ * SDL_UpdateWindowSurface). Defined here for symmetry with the API
+ * surface; the canonical declaration is in SDL_hints.h.
+ *
+ * Values:
+ *  - "1": engine should use the direct-VESA path (when state is valid).
+ *  - "0" / unset / empty: engine should use SDL_UpdateWindowSurface.
+ *
+ * Strict-match per CLAUDE.md DOSKUTSU env-var convention: only the
+ * literal string "1" activates.
+ */
+
+/**
+ * Snapshot of the SDL3-DOS direct-FB fast-path cache (`fb_state`).
+ *
+ * This is a plain data struct returned by value — SDL retains the
+ * authoritative copy in a static singleton inside SDL_dosframebuffer.c;
+ * callers receive a shallow snapshot they can read freely. Do NOT
+ * write through `vram_ptr` or call dosmemput at `vram_phys` after
+ * SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetGeneration() has changed without re-snapshotting:
+ * the underlying mapping or mode may have been freed.
+ *
+ * Field semantics:
+ *
+ *  - `valid`: false if the fast path is not engaged (hint unset, no
+ *    usable VBE access path, mode not yet set). Callers MUST check
+ *    this before reading any other field.
+ *
+ *  - `use_dosmemput`: true → write via dosmemput to a banked window
+ *    (typically 0xA0000); false → write via direct LFB nearptr at
+ *    `vram_ptr`.
+ *
+ *  - `banked_multibank`: true when `fb_size > win_size_bytes`. Single-
+ *    bank banked writes can be a single dosmemput; multi-bank requires
+ *    SDL_DOSVesaDirectBankedFlush() to walk bank boundaries.
+ *
+ *  - `pitches_match`: true when source surface pitch == VBE mode pitch.
+ *    The common case at 320×240×8bpp; row-by-row copy is needed when
+ *    false.
+ *
+ *  - `vram_w`, `vram_h`, `vram_pitch`, `bpp`: VBE mode dimensions and
+ *    bytes-per-pixel. `bpp` is BYTES per pixel (1 for INDEX8, 2 for
+ *    RGB565).
+ *
+ *  - `fb_size`: total framebuffer bytes, `vram_pitch * vram_h`.
+ *
+ *  - `vram_ptr`: LFB nearptr — already includes the BIOS-actual
+ *    display-start offset (patch 0018). NULL when banked path is in
+ *    use (`use_dosmemput=true`). Already-`__djgpp_nearptr_enable`-d
+ *    via DOS_PhysicalToLinear; safe for direct dereference from
+ *    protected mode.
+ *
+ *  - `vram_phys`: banked path → window base address (typically
+ *    `0xA0000`), the `dst` argument for `dosmemput`. LFB path →
+ *    informational copy of the LFB physical address (do NOT pass to
+ *    dosmemput; use `vram_ptr` for memcpy instead).
+ *
+ *  - `win_base`, `win_gran_bytes`, `win_size_bytes`, `win_func_ptr`:
+ *    banked-path metadata, mirroring the VBE mode info. Only valid
+ *    when `use_dosmemput=true`. Pass to SDL_DOSVesaDirectBankedFlush().
+ *
+ *  - `page_offset`: forward-compat field for future page-flipped
+ *    double-buffering. **Always 0 in the current single-buffered build
+ *    (post-patch-0014).** Callers should add this to their `dst_offset`
+ *    on the banked path or to `vram_ptr` arithmetic on the LFB path,
+ *    so future page-flip revival doesn't require engine-side changes.
+ *    Today: no-op math; tomorrow: SDL repopulates this with the
+ *    back-page byte offset.
+ */
+typedef struct SDL_DOSVesaDirectState
+{
+    bool   valid;
+    bool   use_dosmemput;
+    bool   banked_multibank;
+    bool   pitches_match;
+    int    vram_w;
+    int    vram_h;
+    int    vram_pitch;
+    int    bpp;
+    Uint32 fb_size;
+    /* LFB path: */
+    Uint8 *vram_ptr;
+    /* Banked path: */
+    Uint32 vram_phys;
+    Uint32 win_base;
+    Uint32 win_gran_bytes;
+    Uint32 win_size_bytes;
+    Uint32 win_func_ptr;
+    /* Forward-compat (currently always 0): */
+    Uint32 page_offset;
+} SDL_DOSVesaDirectState;
+
+/**
+ * Snapshot the SDL3-DOS direct-FB fast-path state into the caller-supplied
+ * struct.
+ *
+ * Returns true when the fast path is engaged and the snapshot is valid;
+ * false when the fast path is not engaged (hint not set, no window/mode
+ * yet, no usable VBE access path detected). On false return `out->valid`
+ * is also set to false; the other fields are zeroed.
+ *
+ * Cheap to call (a single struct copy + counter read); safe to invoke
+ * once per flip without measurable overhead. Most callers cache the
+ * snapshot and re-call only when SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetGeneration()
+ * changes.
+ *
+ * \param out caller-allocated struct that receives the snapshot.
+ * \returns true if `out->valid==true`, false otherwise.
+ *
+ * \threadsafety Single-threaded; call from the SDL thread.
+ *
+ * \since This function is available since SDL 3.2.0 (DOSKUTSU patch 0034).
+ *
+ * \sa SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetGeneration
+ */
+extern SDL_DECLSPEC bool SDLCALL SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetState(SDL_DOSVesaDirectState *out);
+
+/**
+ * Get the current generation counter for the SDL3-DOS direct-FB cache.
+ *
+ * Bumps monotonically (modulo 2^32) whenever the cached fb_state is
+ * invalidated or re-populated, and on window-framebuffer destruction.
+ * Callers compare against their cached value to cheaply detect mode
+ * changes / lazy-reinit / window-surface re-allocation without polling
+ * the full state.
+ *
+ * Because every code path that re-allocates `window->surface` also
+ * re-runs the populate-fb_state path (CreateWindowFramebuffer →
+ * populate_fb_state_for_direct_fb), a generation bump is also the
+ * signal that the caller's cached `window->surface->pixels` pointer
+ * may be stale. Re-fetch BOTH the snapshot and the surface pointer
+ * on a generation mismatch — no separate heartbeat SDL_RenderPresent
+ * is needed for correctness. See "Mode-change semantics" in the file
+ * doc-comment for the full trigger list.
+ *
+ * \returns the current generation counter.
+ *
+ * \threadsafety Single-threaded.
+ *
+ * \since This function is available since SDL 3.2.0 (DOSKUTSU patch 0034).
+ *
+ * \sa SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetState
+ */
+extern SDL_DECLSPEC Uint32 SDLCALL SDL_DOSVesaDirectGetGeneration(void);
+
+/**
+ * Switch the VBE banked-window selector to a new bank.
+ *
+ * Wraps the SDL3-DOS internal SwitchBank() primitive — uses the BIOS
+ * PMI (`win_func_ptr`) when available, falling back to INT 10h
+ * AX=4F05h with `bx=0` (Window A). Memoizes via the in/out
+ * `current_bank` argument: a no-op when the requested bank is already
+ * active.
+ *
+ * Initialize `*current_bank = -1` once per flush before calling, then
+ * pass the same pointer to subsequent calls (e.g. across multiple
+ * dirty rects in one flush) so consecutive same-bank writes don't
+ * re-issue the bank switch.
+ *
+ * Most callers don't need this directly — SDL_DOSVesaDirectBankedFlush()
+ * handles bank-walking automatically. Use this only when implementing
+ * a custom multi-region flush that benefits from bank reuse across
+ * non-contiguous regions.
+ *
+ * \param bank target bank index (0, 1, ...).
+ * \param current_bank in/out memoization variable; initialize to -1
+ *                     before the first call per flush.
+ * \param win_func_ptr `SDL_DOSVesaDirectState::win_func_ptr` from your
+ *                     snapshot (0 → INT 10h fallback).
+ *
+ * \threadsafety Single-threaded.
+ *
