+ * **SDL itself does NOT consume this hint.** It is registered here for
+ * documentation symmetry with the rest of the DOSKUTSU env-var
+ * convention; the canonical readers are engine-side (e.g. NXEngine-evo's
+ * `Renderer::flip()`). The SDL3-DOS backend always populates fb_state
+ * the same way regardless of this hint — only the engine's choice to
+ * call SDL_DOSVesaDirectPresentFull / SDL_DOSVesaDirectBankedFlush vs
+ * SDL_UpdateWindowSurface depends on it.
+ *
+ * Background: per the wave-18 measurements (real HW Pentium OverDrive 83
+ * MHz + Cirrus + UNIVBE 6.7), `SDL_RenderPresent` adds ~5 ms / flip on
+ * top of the actual VRAM write — the SW-renderer queue flush plus the
