+ *    (default; goes through DOSVESA_UpdateWindowFramebuffer's existing
+ *    fast path).
+ *  - "1": engine should call SDL_DOSVesaDirectPresentFull (or the
+ *    finer-grained SDL_DOSVesaDirectBankedFlush + SDL_memcpy for the
+ *    LFB path) instead of SDL_RenderPresent / SDL_UpdateWindowSurface.
+ *
+ * Strict-match per CLAUDE.md DOSKUTSU env-var convention: only `e[0]=='1'
+ * && e[1]==0` activates. Anything else (including "0", empty string, or
+ * the variable being unset) falls back to the standard present path.
+ *
+ * The engine reads this hint at flip-time (or once at init); the value
+ * can be changed at runtime to A/B-test direct-VESA vs SDL3-render
